Description: Almost complete stone ear- or hair-ring, partly broken off at one end, with a angular edges, triangular in section. On both sides a circumferential line, at the edge perpendicular small parallel lines.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), D14.8A, between levels 1-2
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 137)
